{
  "name": "tandem-tr-85-2-debitcredit-1985-ca207a",
  "title": "A Measure of Transaction Processing Power (Tandem Technical Report 85.2)",
  "description": "Tandem Technical Report 85.2 (February 1985) by 'Anon et al' \u2014 the foundational transaction-processing benchmark paper that defined Sort, Scan, and DebitCredit (ET-1/TP-1) and introduced the Transactions Per Second (TPS) and 5-year capital-cost price/performance metrics. A condensed version appeared in Datamation April 1, 1985. The 'Anon et al' byline concealed a collaboration led by Jim Gray (then at Tandem) with ~24 academics, vendors, and users. This paper is the direct ancestor of the Transaction Processing Performance Council (TPC) benchmarks (TPC-A, TPC-B, TPC-C) and is foundational to Kastner's subsequent career as an OLTP/benchmarks analyst at Stratus and Aberdeen Group.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "created": "2026-04-25",
  "licenses": [
    {
      "name": "CC-BY-4.0",
      "path": "https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"
    }
  ],
